Create a scam-baiting response to the following email, to keep the scammer in a false sense of security by posing as a potential victim.

Dear Beneficiary Cameron McCaffrey,

I am Mrs Judith Anita Williams, the assigned dispatcher for the delivery of your inspected package. As stated in your Package Proof of Delivery (POD) your package contains an ATM Visa Debit Cards with registration No – 834066, weighing 1.4kg as compensation from the USA government in collaboration with the International Monetary Fund.


Your package arrived at our office yesterday with an attached memo of application requesting for the immediate change of the delivering address to 5373 Branciforte Drive Santa Cruz California USA. Please confirm this request through this email address( <PRESIDIO_ANONYMIZED_EMAIL_ADDRESS> ) . Do we proceed delivering to the above submitted address? Get back to me immediately to avoid wrong delivery.

Kindly send your correct information;

Full Name;

Correct House Address;

Telephone Number;

Sex;

Age;

Mrs.Anita Williams

Assigned delivery officer
